All Together

NOTE: this assessment list is DRAFT and SHOULD NOT BE SHARED OUTSIDE OF THE DEPARTMENT

classifications

lake assessments

The number of confirmed and unconfirmed use assessments that contributed to each category.

I filtered the list to only those use assessments that contributed to the segment assessment. Specifically, I filtered it to only those records where the prefix (IR4a) in the segment assessment was also found in the use assessment.

NOTE: there could be more than one use assessment contributing to a segment assessment per PWLID. For example, a lake could be impaired for fishing and primary contact recreation. That lake would be counted in both the fishing and primary contact bars. So you shouldnt add these up to see the total assessments.

source water use

this is the breakdown for all assessments for the source_of_water_supply USE in the draft waterbody inventory NOTE: this assessment list is DRAFT and SHOULD NOT BE SHARED OUTSIDE OF THE DEPARTMENT

and plot how many assessments list dissolved oxygen as the parameter of concern. Repeat for all major parameters.

Please note! a single lake could list both DO and ph as a concern and would contribute to both the DO and PH bars. So dont add these up to count total assessments

Also note, I had to cluster some parameters for easy viewing: 1. Nitrate_Nitrite (nitrate/nitrite, nitrite, nitrate) 2. Metals (iron, manganese, magnesium, copper) 3. Toxics (dioxin; mirex; pcbs; ddt, chlordane; cadmium; pcbs_other_toxics; phenolic_compounds) 4. Solids (silt_sediment; total_dissolved_solids) 5. Problem_Species (problem_species; algal_weed_growth; aquatic_weeds)
